title: Man accused of murdering 22 women is killed by his cellmate
description: A man accused of killing 22 older women has been fatally attacked by his cellmate in a Texas prison.

title: Biden's call to unite behind Ukraine hints at real concern world could succumb to appeasement
description: More than a year and a half into this war, President Biden has felt the need to urge the world not to succumb to appeasement with Russia.

title: Briton among dead after bus plunges into ravine
description: A British national has died after a bus plunged into a ravine in Montenegro, authorities have said.

title: 69 people arrested over 'gay wedding' in Nigeria freed on bail
description: Sixty-nine people arrested after Nigerian police raided an alleged gay wedding have been released on bail.

title: Journalists ordered to leave flood-hit Derna after protests
description: Libyan authorities have ordered some journalists to leave the flood-hit city of Derna, according to a government minister.

title: 'Freedom!': Emotional scenes as five people released in Iran prisoner swap arrive in US
description: Five people released from Iran in a controversial prisoner swap deal with the US have touched down on American soil.

title: World must stand up to Russia's 'naked aggression', Joe Biden warns
description: Joe Biden has said the world must stand up to Russia's "naked aggression" and support the people of Ukraine.

title: What is the Khalistan movement – and how is it linked to rising India-Canada tensions?
description: Relations between India and Canada are at an all-time low after a Sikh leader was shot dead in British Columbia this summer.

title: Azerbaijan targets Armenian positions in Nagorno-Karabakh in 'anti-terrorist operation'
description: Azerbaijan has begun targeting Armenian military positions in the Nagorno-Karabakh region, in what it is calling an "anti-terrorist operation".

title: Starmer and Macron exchange gifts as they meet for first time
description: Sir Keir Starmer and French President Emmanuel Macron have exchanged gifts as they met for the first time.

title: Newcastle fan stabbed in Milan ahead of club's Champions League match
description: A Newcastle fan is in hospital after being stabbed in Milan ahead of the club's Champions League match.

title: Mummified 'alien corpses' are from single skeletons and were not assembled, doctors say
description: Two alleged "non-human" alien corpses each belonged to a single skeleton and were not assembled, Mexican doctors have said.

title: Marilyn Manson fined after blowing nose on camera operator in 2019
description: Rock star Marilyn Manson has been fined and sentenced to 20 hours of community service after pleading no contest to blowing his nose on a camera operator during a concert.

title: Sydney bans fires - including barbecues - as hot and dry conditions bring wildfire risk
description: A total ban on fires - including solid fuel barbecues - is being imposed in Sydney for the first time in almost three years - with the most destructive wildfire season since the "black summer" of 2019-20 being forecast.

title: Take The Money And Run artist ordered to return cash after submitting blank canvasses
description: A Danish artist has been ordered to pay back a museum after it loaned him banknotes worth tens of thousands of pounds for an exhibition he called Take The Money And Run.

title: Jenni Hermoso slams omission from Spain squad
description: The Spanish football federation is trying to divide and manipulate its women players while intimidating and threatening them with "legal repercussions and economic sanctions", Jenni Hermoso has claimed.

title: More than 1 in 10 in Japan now aged 80 or over - after president warned of population crisis
description: More than 1 in 10 people in Japan are aged 80 or older for the first time as the country is increasingly having to deal with an aging population.

title: Elon Musk: This website is free - but not for long
description: Elon Musk has said he will start charging people to use the social media site formerly known as Twitter.

title: India expels Canadian diplomat amid escalating row over the killing of Sikh leader
description: India has expelled a Canadian diplomat amid an escalating row over the killing of Sikh leader Hardeep Singh Nijjar.

title: 'Everything is wrong': Torrent of frustration unleashed in Derna as protesters call for Libyan leadership change
description: The anger in Derna has been brewing for days now. It's been building ever since the floodwaters dropped.
